{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddb203da2-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s211"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"211"},"text":"§ 211.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Rules and regulations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"iddb203da3-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s211/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Comptroller of the Currency may prescribe such rules and regulations as the Comptroller may deem necessary to carry out the provisions of this Act.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"iddb203da4-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s211/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" F.D.I.C. as conservator","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In any case in which the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation is the conservator, any rules or regulations prescribed by the Comptroller shall be consistent with any rules and regulations prescribed by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation pursuant to the Federal Deposit Insurance Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1811"},"text":"12 U.S.C. 1811","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddb203da5-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1933-03-09/ch1"},"text":"Mar. 9, 1933, ch. 1","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 211, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/5"},"text":"48 Stat. 5","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73/tVIII/s807"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73, title VIII, § 807","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1989-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 1989","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/103/446"},"text":"103 Stat. 446","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddb203da6-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddb203da7-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddb203da8-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This Act, referred to in subsec. (a), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1933-03-09/ch1"},"text":"act Mar. 9, 1933, ch. 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/1"},"text":"48 Stat. 1","children":[],"tail":", popularly known as the Emergency Banking and Bank Conservation Act, which is classified to sections 51a, 51b, 51c, 51d, 95, 201 to 212, 248, 347b, 347c, 347d, and 445 of this title and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s4305"},"text":"section 4305 of Title 50","children":[],"tail":", War and National Defense, and classified as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t50/s4305"},"text":"section 4305 of Title 50","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s51d"},"text":"Section 51d of this title","children":[],"tail":" was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-06-30/ch166/tII/s206/b"},"text":"act June 30, 1947, ch. 166, title II, § 206(b)","children":[],"tail":", ("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"o","children":[],"tail":"), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/208"},"text":"61 Stat. 208","children":[],"tail":". For effect of the repeal on outstanding debentures held by banks, see References in Text note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s51b–1"},"text":"section 51b–1 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Deposit Insurance Act, referred to in subsec. (b), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-09-21/ch967/s2"},"text":"act Sept. 21, 1950, ch. 967, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/873"},"text":"64 Stat. 873","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 16 (§ 1811 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1811"},"text":"section 1811 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddb203da9-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/73"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–73","children":[],"tail":" amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section read as follows: “The Comptroller of the Currency is authorized and empowered, with the approval of the Secretary of the Treasury, to prescribe such rules and regulations as he may deem necessary in order to carry out the provisions of this subchapter. Whoever violates any rule or regulation made pursuant to this section shall be deemed guilty of a misdemeanor and, upon conviction thereof, shall be fined not more than $5,000, or imprisoned not more than one year, or both.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"iddb203daa-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"iddb203dab-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Exception as to Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions vested by any provision of law in Comptroller of the Currency, referred to in this section, not included in transfer of functions to Secretary of the Treasury, see note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1"},"text":"section 1 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
